Hello, 
I've recently downloaded atom and started writing c++ code on it. It's amazing although one thing, when starting a class, closing brackets does not have a semicolon. It just looks like this
`#include <iostream>
class Something {
public: //something
private: //something
} //should have semicolon

int main {
  /_something_/
}`

Where is this option over atom? 

```
// Set to true to insert spaces when tab is pressed
"translate_tabs_to_spaces": false,

// If translate_tabs_to_spaces is true, use_tab_stops will make tab and
// backspace insert/delete up to the next tabstop
"use_tab_stops": false,
```

It is simple, it is horrible to this editor keep deleting all my dear 4 spaces every time I hit the delete button.
